Different methods were used to cluster Chinese cities to discuss previous city-level emissions. For example, Ramaswami 
 et al. (
 
  15
 ) used GDP share to classify 285 Chinese cities into 38 industrial cities, 44 commercial cities, and 203 mixed-economy cities. Such a taxonomy method is further developed based on Nelson (
 
  59
 ) and is widely used in city-level research.
